BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:96948@moodle.humphreys.edu
SUMMARY:Assignment #2 (Wk3: Exec Summary) is due
DESCRIPTION:You are the top advisor to your country’s president. Citizens h
	ave voiced growing concerns about the loss of privacy in today’s technology
	-driven society. They feel increasingly monitored—through cameras\, phone u
	sage\, and online activity—and believe this erosion of privacy is affecting
	 their quality of life.\n\nWith a presidential election approaching in six 
	months\, the president plans to release a policy paper titled _“The Rights 
	of Our Citizens.”_ This policy will address privacy related to financial\, 
	health\, and other personal data. However\, it must also ensure that busine
	sses can continue to access consumer data needed to understand purchasing b
	ehavior and sustain economic growth. The policy must therefore strike a car
	eful balance between individual privacy and business needs.\n\nAs the top a
	dvisor\, you are required to write a 2-3 PAGE policy paper that addresses t
	he following:\n\n	* Issue background: Overview of the current privacy lands
	cape\n	* Impact on citizens: How the perceived loss of data privacy affects
	 individuals\n	* Impact on business: Why access to personal data is importa
	nt for businesses\n	* Rights of citizens: Define consumer rights related to
	 data privacy\n	* Rights of businesses: Define consumer rights related to d
	ata privacy\n	* Proposed law: Recommend a balanced policy that protects sen
	sitive data while allowing appropriate data use to support business and eco
	nomic growth\n\nYour paper should meet the following structural requirement
	s:\n\n	* 2-3 pages in length (excluding the title and reference pages)\n	* 
	Support your statements with IN-TEXT citations from a minimum of 2 scholarl
	y articles from class readings\, textbook\, or lectures\n\n
	
CLASS:PUBLIC
LAST-MODIFIED:20260409T014456Z
DTSTAMP:20260417T030052Z
DTSTART:20260427T065900Z
DTEND:20260427T065900Z
CATEGORIES:2026SP-MBA394B
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:96958@moodle.humphreys.edu
SUMMARY:DF (Wk3: Privacy) is due
DESCRIPTION:This week's topic pertains to privacy. As consumers\, we demand
	 privacy. On the other hand\, producers want to collect as much information
	 as they can about their potential customers for targeted consumer marketin
	g. \n\nFacebook has done this very effectively. It has created systems that
	 can track a user's online activity and\, subsequently\, tailor their adver
	tisements. You may have noticed that\, shortly after you search for plane f
	ares\, airline advertisements popup on Google and Facebook.\n\nDiscuss what
	 is meant by the term “privacy” in relation to customers (and people in gen
	eral). What is the level of privacy and confidentiality one should expect o
	r have? Do we need to waive our privacy rights when we perform an online se
	arch or use a phone app?\n\nProvide one original post\, along with 2 respon
	ses to the posts made by other students. Each response should be a minimum 
	of 2 paragraphs. Your original post must include at least two citations.\n
	
CLASS:PUBLIC
LAST-MODIFIED:20260401T210407Z
DTSTAMP:20260417T030052Z
DTSTART:20260427T065900Z
DTEND:20260427T065900Z
CATEGORIES:2026SP-MBA394B
END:VEVENT
